{"id":34518,"date":"2024-01-23T20:42:00","date_gmt":"2022-05-23T15:12:00","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/?p=34518"},"modified":"2023-03-31T15:11:54","modified_gmt":"2023-03-31T09:41:54","slug":"modern-villa-design","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/modern-villa-design\/","title":{"rendered":"Your Guide To Planning A Modern Villa\u2019s Interior Design"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Having your own villa is every homeowner\u2019s dream, especially when we are forced to live in shoe-box size apartments to stay close to our workspace. If you are one of the fortunate ones who are the proud owners of a villa, why not transform it into a tech-savvy and environment-friendly abode with a modern villa design?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Due to its massive area, designing the interiors of a villa is quite different from designing an apartment. It can take an army to plan and design the entrance, courtyard (if you have one), living room, master bedroom and ensuite, guest rooms, guest bathrooms, dry and wet kitchens, formal dining room, terrace or deck, and landscaping! So, to help you plan the look and interiors of your villa, here are some of the best modern villa designs for inspiration.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Set The Tone Of Your Modern Villa Design With A Luxurious Living Room<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The most significant upside of having your own villa is you can build high ceilings. It makes the room look bigger and more spacious. So, use the height to your advantage by installing a long designer chandelier. You can also add long curtains for a grander look. Multiple modular sofas and accent chairs easily increase the seating options. It especially comes in handy when you\u2019re hosting many guests. Turn your living room into an entertainment zone by placing a modular TV unit and mounting a large TV on the wall. The floor to ceiling wooden panelling on the walls further makes the living room aesthetically appealing.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/08180759\/set-the-tone-of-your-modern-villa-design-with-a-luxurious-living-room.jpg\" alt=\"Set the tone of your modern villa design with a luxurious living room.jpg\" class=\"wp-image-34519\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/08180759\/set-the-tone-of-your-modern-villa-design-with-a-luxurious-living-room.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/08180759\/set-the-tone-of-your-modern-villa-design-with-a-luxurious-living-room-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/08180759\/set-the-tone-of-your-modern-villa-design-with-a-luxurious-living-room-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/08180759\/set-the-tone-of-your-modern-villa-design-with-a-luxurious-living-room-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>A multipurpose living room is the heart of your home<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">The Elegant Dining Room Of A Modern Villa Design Plan<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>For modern contemporary villa designs, you need a stylish dining room that makes it the talk of the party. The dark theme of this dining room adds drama and glam to your villa. The all-black 6-seater dining table with luxurious suede chairs and light wooden flooring give the room a fashionable contrast. Meanwhile, tinted glassware and a designer chandelier go well in the white room that features a Victorian green accent wall. No doubt, this luxury dining room will be the centre of attraction in your modern villa.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/08180758\/the-elegant-dining-room-of-a-small-modern-villa-design-plan.jpg\" alt=\"The elegant dining room of a small modern villa design plan\" class=\"wp-image-34520\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/08180758\/the-elegant-dining-room-of-a-small-modern-villa-design-plan.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/08180758\/the-elegant-dining-room-of-a-small-modern-villa-design-plan-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/08180758\/the-elegant-dining-room-of-a-small-modern-villa-design-plan-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/08180758\/the-elegant-dining-room-of-a-small-modern-villa-design-plan-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Break the monotony with an enigmatic dining room<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">An Easy-To-Navigate Kitchen Layout For Modern Villa Interior Design<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>A spacious kitchen is a must in a villa. Modern villa designs in India must include lots of storage options for groceries and appliances to make the kitchen look clutter-free. The kitchen counter in this design is L-shaped with lots of drawers and cabinets along with wall-mounted covered cabinets to increase storage space. Plus, the massive island can be used in multiple ways. You can use it as a breakfast nook and add more storage below by having cabinets and a small shelf. What makes the kitchen even bigger and airy are the large picture windows. You can add a small dining table by the windows if you want to enjoy the view with your meals.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/08180756\/an-easy-to-navigate-kitchen-layout-for-best-modern-villa-designs.jpg\" alt=\"An easy-to-navigate kitchen layout for best modern villa designs\" class=\"wp-image-34521\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/08180756\/an-easy-to-navigate-kitchen-layout-for-best-modern-villa-designs.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/08180756\/an-easy-to-navigate-kitchen-layout-for-best-modern-villa-designs-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/08180756\/an-easy-to-navigate-kitchen-layout-for-best-modern-villa-designs-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/08180756\/an-easy-to-navigate-kitchen-layout-for-best-modern-villa-designs-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>The kitchen is where all the magic happens<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Bedroom Of A Modern Luxury Villa Design To Retire Comfortably<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>When you retire to your bed at the end of a hard day at work, its vibe should be calming. That\u2019s why the master bedroom should be designed thoughtfully. It not only should be airy and hold a large king-size bed, but it should also reflect your personal taste. The master bedroom of a modern luxury villa design should include an extra lounge area, a TV unit and possibly a small study nook if you need to get some work done quickly. Large floor to ceiling curtains make the room look bigger. Wall panelling is also in trend. You can use it to create a gallery wall or DIY with printed wallpaper.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/08180755\/bedroom-of-a-modern-luxury-villa-design-to-retire-comfortably.jpg\" alt=\"Bedroom of a modern luxury villa design to retire comfortably\" class=\"wp-image-34522\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/08180755\/bedroom-of-a-modern-luxury-villa-design-to-retire-comfortably.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/08180755\/bedroom-of-a-modern-luxury-villa-design-to-retire-comfortably-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/08180755\/bedroom-of-a-modern-luxury-villa-design-to-retire-comfortably-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/08180755\/bedroom-of-a-modern-luxury-villa-design-to-retire-comfortably-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>A spacious, luxurious and relaxing master bedroom<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Bathrooms Make All The Difference<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>When you are planning for a modern villa interior design, don\u2019t forget to design a spacious bathroom with a bathtub. And why not! You have enough space to install one. So, on weekends you can soak up and truly enjoy yourself. But, if you are not a bathtub person, then we suggest you install a separate walk-in shower. For storage, a wall-mounted modular cabinet works really well.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/08180751\/bathrooms-make-all-the-difference-in-a-modern-villa-design.jpg\" alt=\"Bathrooms make all the difference in a a modern villa design\" class=\"wp-image-34524\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/08180751\/bathrooms-make-all-the-difference-in-a-modern-villa-design.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/08180751\/bathrooms-make-all-the-difference-in-a-modern-villa-design-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/08180751\/bathrooms-make-all-the-difference-in-a-modern-villa-design-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/08180751\/bathrooms-make-all-the-difference-in-a-modern-villa-design-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Relax in a luxurious bathroom in your modern villa<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Enjoy Breezy Evenings In Your Balcony Bar Area<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Enjoy your evenings while sipping a glass of your favourite wine on your balcony. When you\u2019re planning your modern villa design, don\u2019t forget to add a modular bar unit along with a few high chairs, some plants, string lights and comfy lounge chairs. These elements and accessories can completely change the vibe of your balcony. This can be another focal point of your modern villa interior design.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/08180749\/enjoy-breezy-evening-in-balcony-bar-area-in-a-modern-villa-design.jpg\" alt=\"Enjoy breezy evening in balcony bar area in a modern villa design\" class=\"wp-image-34525\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/08180749\/enjoy-breezy-evening-in-balcony-bar-area-in-a-modern-villa-design.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/08180749\/enjoy-breezy-evening-in-balcony-bar-area-in-a-modern-villa-design-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/08180749\/enjoy-breezy-evening-in-balcony-bar-area-in-a-modern-villa-design-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/08180749\/enjoy-breezy-evening-in-balcony-bar-area-in-a-modern-villa-design-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Give your balcony a relaxing vibe<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Did you like these modern villa design ideas? We hope you found inspiration in them. If you have any questions, our expert designers are here to help you navigate. Click <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/\">here<\/a> to contact us.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<d